# Statements

Let a statement stand for a set. Let P denote a statement.

Let P(x) stand for x is an element of P. Let P holds for x stand for P(x).

Let "P" stand for P holds for every object.

Let FALSE stand for contradiction.
Let TRUE  stand for not FALSE.


# Arities of statements

Signature. P has no free variable is an atom.

Signature. P has one free variable is an atom.

Definition. P has at most one free variable iff P is a statement or P has one
free variable.

Signature. P has two free variables is an atom. Let P(x,y) stand for P((x,y)).


Axiom. Let x,y,a,b be objects. If (a,b) = (x,y) then a = x and b = y.
